trong><br /> •Participate in coverage for the 24-hour hotline and medical advocacy services.<br /> •Support web-based chat services for survivor access.<br /> •Once trained, contribute to the delivery of company’s internal RCC training.</p> <p> <strong>Fundraising and Donor Engagement</strong><br /> •Design and support the annual fundraising plan with clear financial and donor engagement objectives.<br /> Oversee individual donor cultivation and maintain relationships with current and potential donors.<br /> •Build company’s grassroots fundraising strategies with an emphasis on diversifying income.<br /> •Coordinate with the Executive Director in managing donor and foundation relationships.<br /> •Maintain donor databases to track engagement and acknowledgments.<br /> •Assist with scheduling donor and foundation meetings.<br /> •Collaborate with the communications team on donor appeals, marketing materials, acknowledgments, and follow-up.<br /> •Attend community events as an ambassador for the company.<br /> •Staff and support the Board Development Committee in advancing engagement and fundraising efforts.<br /> •Perform other related duties as assigned by the direct supervisor.</p> <p> <strong>Qualifications:</strong><br /> •Bachelor’s Degree in field of social work, psychology, community organizing, violence prevention or comparable lived experience.<br /> •5+ years’ experience in the health and social service field<br /> •2-4 years in program management/supervision<br /> •Demonstrated experience developing and implementing culturally relevant programs for diverse cultural and linguistic populations<br /> •Proficiency with MS Office, Outlook, Google Docs, Bloomerang, etc.<br /> •Expertise in program evaluation, outcomes, and measurement systems<br /> •Ability to work evenings and weekends as needed<br /> •Experience with group presentations, providing training and technical assistance<br /> •Dynamic community organizer, able to transfer knowledge to staff<br /> •Excellent public speaking, presentation skill, and communication skills both verbal/written<br /> •Bilingual in Spanish, Khmer and/or Haitian Creole, highly desired<br /> •Trained RCC Counselor or ability to begin Rape Crisis Counselor training within 1 month of hire<br /> •Proficiency in MS Office and professional experience with Social Media applications</p> <p> </p> <p><span>#zip</span></p> ]]>
