andards. <li>Collaborate with Logistics staff to stage shipments and prepare materials for outbound freight. <li>Participate in rigging and safe handling of heavy or oversized materials. </ul> <p>Education, Training, and Experience:</p> <ol> <li>8+ years of progressive experience in warehouse or logistics operations, ideally in regulated industries. <li>Proficiency with ERP systems, MS Office (Word, Excel, Outlook), and data entry.? <li>Excellent communication, problem-solving, attention to detail, and the ability to work both independently and as part of a team.? <li>Powered industrial truck (PIT) certification for forklifts, scissor jacks, and Crown Wave order pickers. <li>Experience in lean manufacturing processes and improvements <li>Experience in crating product with custom non-standard packaging with vapor barrier sealing. <li>Strong problem-solving, organizational, and communication skills. <li>Demonstrated ability to execute tasks independently and train junior staff. </ol> <p>Physical and Environmental Considerations:</p> <ul> <li>Must be able to sit/stand for long periods of time. <li>Required use of standard office equipment including laptop, phone, copier, etc. <li>Must be able to safely navigate factory and warehouse environments. <li>May be involved in rigging operations and heavy equipment handling. <li>Must be able to work in confined spaces or areas requiring use of a harness. <li>Ability to lift 25-pound boxes to a height of 3–4 feet. <li>Ability to push & pull heavy pallets with a hand truck. <li>Able to reach, bend, and move safely in warehouse settings. </ul> <p> </p> <p>#toponehire</p> ]]>
