ed processes.</p> <li> <p>Ensure compliance with aerospace regulatory frameworks including EAR, ITAR, DFARS, and customer-specific requirements.</p> <li> <p>Support audits and maintain documentation in alignment with quality standards.</p> </ul> <hr> <h2>Qualifications</h2> <h3>Education</h3> <ul> <li> <p>Bachelor’s degree (BS/BA) from an accredited college or university.</p> </ul> <h3>Experience</h3> <ul> <li> <p>Minimum of 5–7 years of progressive supply chain or purchasing experience.</p> <li> <p>Aerospace manufacturing experience strongly preferred.</p> <li> <p>Demonstrated experience operating within regulated environments (EAR, ITAR, DFARS).</p> </ul> <h3>Skills & Competencies</h3> <ul> <li> <p>Excellent verbal and written communication skills.</p> <li> <p>Strong interpersonal and conflict resolution abilities.</p> <li> <p>Exceptional organizational skills with high attention to detail.</p> <li> <p>Advanced analytical and problem-solving skills.</p> <li> <p>Proven ability to manage and develop supply chain partnerships.</p> <li> <p>Strong understanding of aerospace regulatory requirements and quality systems.</p> <li> <p>Proficiency in Microsoft Office Suite and ERP/MRP systems.</p> </ul> <hr> <h2>Training Requirements</h2> <ul> <li> <p>Employee Orientation</p> <li> <p>Annual Safety Training</p> <li> <p>Annual Quality Procedures Training</p> <li> <p>Job-Specific Skills Training</p> <li> <p>Training as mandated by the State of Connecticut</p> </ul> <hr> <h2>Working Conditions</h2> <ul> <li> <p>Work environment includes both office and manufacturing settings.</p> <li> <p>Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) required in manufacturing areas:</p> <ul> <li> <p>Safety glasses with side shields</p> <li> <p>Safety shoes</p> </ul> <li> <p>Maximum lift requirement: 15 lbs.</p> </ul> <hr> <h2>Why Join Us</h2> <p>This is a key role within a growing aerospace organization where the Senior Buyer will directly impact operational performance, supplier strategy, and production readiness. The position offers strong visibility within Operations and the opportunity to contribute to strategic supply chain initiatives.</p> <p> </p> <p>#toponehire</p> ]]>
