rong>Requirements:</strong></span></span></p> <ul> <li><span><span>High school diploma or equivalent required, college degree preferred.</span></span> <li><span><span>At least 3 years of experience in medical insurance and billing, preferably in the specialized area of behavioral health</span></span> <li><span><span>Knowledge/understanding of deductibles, copay, coinsurance, prior authorizations, referrals, etc. is required.</span></span> <li><span><span>Ability to pay close attention to accuracy and detail in all facets of the position.</span></span> <li><span><span>Self-starter with a sense of urgency and proven ability to take ownership of job responsibilities and ensure successful completion of all projects and requests.</span></span> <li><span><span>Must demonstrate good oral and written communication skills with strong listening/comprehension skills.</span></span> <li><span><span>Ability to effectively prioritize and multi-task in high volume workload situations and meet all deadlines.</span></span> <li><span><span>Excellent interpersonal skills in a team environment</span></span> <li><span><span>Ability to manage competing and adjusting priorities.</span></span> <li><span><span>Ability to adjust responsibilities to accommodate a fast-paced work environment while maintaining excellent patient, vendor and staff interactions.</span></span> <li><span><span>Ability to interact with patients and insurance representatives throughout the day in person, as well as via phone and computer.</span></span> <li><span><span>Proficient in a Microsoft Windows Environment including Microsoft Office</span></span> <li><span><span>Understanding of Confidentiality</span></span> <li><span><span>Proficiency with EMR systems, particularly Lytec</span></span> </ul> <p> …Pay Statement and Pay Transparency Laws: rate of pay listed is on a per hour basis. You will be entitled to health insurance once employed for 60 days and you must work 30 hours per week, on average, per month to enroll