ions, and document care appropriately</p> <li> <p>Complete disability and insurance documentation</p> <li> <p>Maintain surgical logs and assist with clinical documentation</p> <li> <p>Participate in clinical research and educational initiatives as assigned</p> <li> <p>Successfully complete EHR system training (EPIC)</p> </ul> <p><strong>Minimum Qualifications</strong></p> <ul> <li> <p>Graduate of an accredited Physician Assistant program</p> <li> <p>Current New York State Physician Assistant license</p> <li> <p>BLS and ACLS certification</p> <li> <p>Strong clinical assessment, diagnostic, and patient management skills</p> <li> <p>Ability to work collaboratively in a fast-paced, high-volume setting</p> <li> <p>Reliable transportation for travel between multiple office locations</p> </ul> <p><strong>Preferred Qualifications</strong></p> <ul> <li> <p>Master’s degree</p> <li> <p>Prior orthopedic surgery experience, particularly in sports medicine and/or shoulder and elbow</p> <li> <p>Experience in both outpatient clinical and operating room environments</p> <li> <p>Spanish fluency</p> </ul> <p><strong>Compensation & Benefits</strong></p> <ul> <li> <p>Comprehensive benefits package</p> <li> <p>Collaborative, physician-led environment</p> <li> <p>Strong clinical learning and growth opportunity</p> </ul> <p>#zip</p> ]]>
