<![CDATA[ <h2> Planner II – Littleton, MA – $85K</p> <p> Description</h2> <p><strong>Position Summary</strong></p> <p>The Planner II is responsible for end-to-end planning and execution of material and production plans for complex, long-lead, engineered-to-order medical systems and service assemblies. This role operates at the system and project level, translating MRP outputs, engineering releases, and SIOP commitments into executable production plans that support on-time system delivery, service fulfillment, and regulatory compliance. The Planner II acts as a cross-functional integrator, working closely with Manufacturing, Purchasing, Engineering, Quality, and Program Management to manage schedules, material readiness, and execution risk across assigned systems or service programs.</p> <p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p> <ul> <li>Develop and maintain system-level production plans aligned to approved SIOP and master schedules <li>Create, release, and manage work orders, jobs, and build packages in ERP/MRP systems <li>Plan and sequence production activities across manufacturing cells, commissioning, and test phases <li>Own material readiness for assigned systems, including long-lead and critical components </ul> <ul> <li>Analyze MRP outputs to identify shortages, constraints, and risks <li>Coordinate with Purchasing on PO placement, expediting, and supplier recovery actions <li>Maintain accurate planning parameters (lead times, order policies, safety stock where applicable) <li>Support BOM integrity by validating planning alignment to released engineering configurations </ul> <ul> <li>Serve as the primary planning interface for assigned systems or service programs <li>Partner with Engineering to manage ECO impacts to active builds and schedules <li>Work with Manufacturing Supervisors to balance capacity, priorities, and labor constraints <li>Support Program Management with schedule inputs, risks, and recovery plans </ul> <ul> <li>Track execution against plan and proactively identify schedule and material risks <li>Lead or support mitigation plans for shortages, delays, or scope changes <li>Escalate issues through Tier I / Tier II operational governance as appropriate <li>Maintain clear ownership and documentation of planning assumptions and decisions </ul> <ul> <li>Maintain planning-related KPIs (e.g., WO on-time release, material availability, schedule adherence) <li>Support Tier meeting reporting and visual management boards <li>Identify opportunities to improve planning processes, data accuracy, and system utilization <li>Contribute to standard work development and planning best practices </ul> <p> </p> <p><strong>Required Qualifications</strong></p> <ul> <li>Bachelor’s degree in Supply Chain, Operations Management, Engineering, or related field<br /> <em>(or equivalent experience in manufacturing planning)</em> <li>3–6 years of experience in production planning, material planning, or supply chain execution <li>Experience working in engineered-to-order, project-based, or regulated manufacturing environments <li>Strong working knowledge of ERP/MRP systems (e.g., Salesforce, Oracle, SAP, Epicor, NetSuite, etc.) <li>Proficiency in Excel (pivot tables, formulas, basic data analysis) </ul> <p><strong>Preferred Qualifications</strong></p> <ul> <li>Experience in medical device, capital equipment, aerospace, or defense manufacturing <li>Familiarity with SIOP / Master Scheduling concepts <li>Understanding of BOM structures, ECO workflows, and configuration control <li>APICS/ASCM certification (CPIM, CSCP) or progress toward certification <li>Experience supporting service operations or installed-base programs </ul> <p>#toponehire</p> ]]>
