he configuration and customization of applications to meet evolving business needs. <li>Supports the implementation of new features, modules, and system upgrades. <li>Provides training and ongoing support to end users on enterprise application functionality and best practices. <li>Creates and maintains comprehensive technical documentation including system configurations, integration specifications, and troubleshooting guides. <li>Develops user guides, knowledge base articles, and training materials for various stakeholder groups. <li>Conducts training sessions and workshops for new system features and enhancements for technical team(s). <li>Participates in application implementation projects from planning through go-live and post-implementation support. <li>Identifies opportunities for process optimization, automation, and system efficiency improvements. <li>Collaborates with vendors and third-party providers to resolve technical issues and implement new capabilities. <li>Maintains project documentation and ensures deliverables meet established timelines and quality standards. <li>Builds and maintains seamless data flows between legal applications and enterprise systems like iManage, Aderant, Okta, Microsoft 365, etc. </ul> <p><strong>ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS:</strong></p> <ul> <li>Provides technical support and maintenance for mission-critical enterprise applications with minimal downtime. <li>Develops and maintains SQL queries, reports, and data extracts for business intelligence and operational needs. <li>Meets project deliverable deadlines and service level agreements for incident resolution. <li>Coordinates with vendors for issue escalation, patch management, and system upgrades. <li>Monitors application metrics and implements proactive maintenance procedures for performance issues and improvements. <li>Maintains version control and change management documentation for all system modifications. <li>Performs application testing including unit testing, integration testing, and user acceptance testing support for new installs, updates, and patches. <li>Creates and updates documentation for system controls, updates and support for the enterprise applications and custom integrations. <li>Performs other duties as assigned. </ul> <p><strong>QUALIFICATIONS:</strong></p> <ul> <li>Bachelor’s degree or equivalent in Computer Science or a related field preferred. <li>Minimum of five (5+) years of work experience in the field of application support for legal applications, or equivalent combination of education and work experience. <li>Minimum of five (5+) years of experience installing, supporting, and upgrading back-end databases and enterprise class, multi-user software applications (either on-premises or cloud-based) <li>Possesses strong understanding of enterprise software architecture, legal technology systems, and the ability to collaborate effectively with various teams to support strategic objectives. <li>Ability to solve more complex problems by analyzing variables and applying appropriate solutions learned through professional experience and proficiency. <li>Knowledge of document management (iManage or NetDocuments), financial applications (Aderant), and IP management software (CPi and IPDAS). <li>Highly proficient in MS Outlook, Word, and Excel as well as basic computer and database management skills. <li>Proficiency in SQL database management and query development. <li>Experience with scripting languages (PowerShell, Python, or similar) for automation, (Okta workflow knowledge helpful) <li>Knowledge of enterprise application architecture, web services, and API integrations <li>Familiarity with Azure, AWS, or other cloud platforms. <li>Understanding of authentication protocols (SAML, OAuth, Active Directory) <li>Experience with reporting tools, (Power BI, Tableau, etc.). <li>Exceptional oral and written communication skills and the ability to effectively communicate workflow and project updates. <li>Strong interpersonal skills and ability to work effectively with various levels of constituencies. <li>Ability to work independently and with a team. <li>Flexibility and capacity to respond calmly and efficiently in stressful situations. </ul> <p>#toponehire</p> ]]>
