pliance</p> </ul> <p><em>Professional Development / Education:</em></p> <ul> <li> <p>Participate in ongoing learning, workshops, and conferences</p> <li> <p>Act as a preceptor or mentor to staff and students</p> <li> <p>Maintain collaborative practice agreements as required by law</p> <li> <p>Engage in professional organizations and community initiatives</p> </ul> <p><em>Communication / Relationships:</em></p> <ul> <li> <p>Demonstrate professionalism, courtesy, and respect in interactions with patients, families, and staff</p> <li> <p>Collaborate effectively with interdisciplinary teams and community agencies</p> <li> <p>Report to the medical director or supervisory leadership as required</p> </ul> <p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p> <ul> <li> <p>Bachelor’s and Master’s degree in Nursing</p> <li> <p>Graduate of an accredited Nurse Practitioner program</p> <li> <p>Current NY State RN license and NP certification/registration</p> <li> <p>Current BCLS certification</p> <li> <p>Strong clinical experience as a Family Nurse Practitioner</p> <li> <p>Basic computer skills; familiarity with electronic health records preferred</p> <li> <p>Bilingual in Spanish preferred</p> </ul> <p><strong>Additional Skills:</strong></p> <ul> <li> <p>Effective problem-solving, organizational, leadership, and interpersonal skills</p> <li> <p>Commitment to patient-centered care and health promotion</p> </ul> <p>#zip</p> ]]>
