s and leadership to support business initiatives. </ul> <hr> <h3>What You’ll Bring:</h3> <p>We’re looking for a team player who’s detail-oriented, adaptable, and ready to roll up their sleeves.</p> <p><strong>Key qualifications:</strong></p> <ul> <li>Bachelor’s degree in Accounting, Finance, or a related field (required). <li>At least 6 years of accounting/finance experience, with 1+ years in a supervisory role. <li>Background in public accounting (required). <li>CPA license (preferred but not required). <li>Experience in inventory or manufacturing accounting (a plus). <li>Familiarity with accounting software such as QuickBooks or Sage (helpful). <li>Excellent communication skills and ability to thrive in a fast-paced environment. </ul> <hr> <h3>What Sets This Role Apart:</h3> <ul> <li><strong>Collaborative Culture:</strong> A welcoming, team-focused environment where relationships matter. <li><strong>Growth Opportunity:</strong> A chance to make your mark in a rapidly scaling company backed by a respected private equity partner. <li><strong>Hybrid Flexibility:</strong> Enjoy a balanced work schedule with remote flexibility. </ul> <p>#toponehire</p> ]]>
