g</p> <li> <p>Experience caring for diverse patient populations</p> <li> <p>Excellent communication and interpersonal skills</p> <li> <p>Proficiency with electronic health records and clinical technology</p> <li> <p>Strong organizational skills and attention to detail</p> </ul> <p> </p> <h3><strong>Preferred Qualifications</strong></h3> <ul> <li> <p>3+ years of experience in an ambulatory or urgent care setting preferred</p> <li> <p>Experience working with underserved or socioeconomically diverse populations</p> <li> <p>Bilingual (Spanish/English) candidates strongly preferred</p> </ul> <hr> <h3><strong>Compensation & Benefits</strong></h3> <ul> <li> <p>Competitive base salary with productivity bonus potential</p> <li> <p>Eligibility for federal loan repayment programs</p> <li> <p>Paid malpractice insurance and CME allowance</p> <li> <p>Medical, dental, and vision insurance</p> <li> <p>401(k) with employer match</p> <li> <p>Generous paid time off</p> <li> <p>Paid holidays</p> <li> <p>Employer-paid life insurance</p> <li> <p>Short-term and long-term disability coverage</p> <li> <p>Employee Assistance Program</p> <li> <p>Workers’ compensation coverage</p> <li> <p>Multiple paid leave options, including parental, military, and bereavement leave</p> </ul> <p>#zip</p> ]]>
