uding CPR/First Aid</p> <li> <p>Strong interpersonal skills with the ability to build effective working relationships</p> <li> <p>Ability to read, analyze, and interpret client information, clinical documentation, and education plans</p> <li> <p>Ability to reason through practical problems and interpret instructions in various formats</p> <li> <p>Cultural competency across diverse populations</p> <li> <p>Bilingual or clinical competencies as applicable to the role</p> </ul> <h3>Additional Requirements</h3> <ul> <li> <p>Valid driver’s license and reliable vehicle</p> <li> <p>Willingness to travel locally to foster homes, schools, and community sites</p> <li> <p>Ability to complete MAPP training and certification to train Spanish-speaking foster care providers in medication administration</p> <li> <p>Proof of adequate personal auto insurance, including required bodily injury and property damage coverage</p> </ul> <h3>Benefits</h3> <ul> <li> <p>Medical and dental insurance</p> <li> <p>Employer-paid group term life insurance</p> <li> <p>Health Savings Account (HSA) and Medical/Dependent FSA</p> <li> <p>Voluntary benefits including accident, critical illness, hospital indemnity, and identity theft protection</p> <li> <p>401(k) with employer match after one year of service</p> <li> <p>On-site gym, wellness/relaxation chamber, and employee discounts</p> </ul> <p>#toponehire</p> ]]>
