rive continuous improvement initiatives aimed at reducing incidents, near-misses, and overall environmental risk.</span></span> </ul> <p><span><span><strong>Facilities Management</strong></span></span></p> <ul> <li><span><span>Maintenance Oversight: Supervise routine facility maintenance, emergency repairs, and <a href="https://www.google.com/search?q=https://www.reliableplant.com/preventive-maintenance-31970" target="_blank">preventive maintenance programs</a> to ensure zero downtime.</span></span> <li><span><span>Contractor Coordination: Manage relationships and performance for all external contractors and specialized service providers.</span></span> <li><span><span>Project Support: Provide safety and facility expertise for capital improvement projects, ensuring all upgrades meet technical and regulatory standards.</span></span> </ul> <div> <hr> </div> <p><span><span><strong>Required Qualifications</strong></span></span></p> <ul> <li><span><span>Experience: 7+ years of relevant EHS experience within a manufacturing, industrial, or highly regulated environment.</span></span> <li><span><span>Education: Bachelor’s degree in Environmental Health & Safety, Industrial Hygiene, Safety Engineering, Environmental Science, or a related technical field.</span></span> <li><span><span>Certifications: Professional certifications such as ASP (Associate Safety Professional), CSP, CHMM, or CIH are highly preferred (or actively in progress).</span></span> </ul> <p><span><span><strong>Skills & Competencies</strong></span></span></p> <ul> <li><span><span>Deep technical knowledge of federal and local environmental and safety laws.</span></span> <li><span><span>Proven ability to lead <a href="https://www.osha.gov/incident-investigation" target="_blank">incident investigations</a> and implement long-term safety solutions.</span></span> <li><span><span>Strong project management skills with the ability to oversee complex facility repairs and upgrades.</span></span> <li><span><span>Excellent communication skills for interfacing with both shop-floor employees and high-level regulatory officials.</span></span> </ul> <p><span><span><span>#toponehire</span></span></span></p> ]]>
