<![CDATA[ <p><strong>Position:</strong> Dental Hygienist<br /> <strong>Pay Rate: $42-$50</strong> per hour<br /> Duration: 3 Months<br /> <strong>Location:</strong> Norwalk CT<br /> <strong>Monday- Friday with one Saturday per month<br /> Open to full time or even part time 2 days a week</p> <p> Job Summary:</strong></p> <p>Provides prescribed dental hygiene/periodontal services to patients in a caring and professional manner.  Perform all necessary oral prophylactic services including initial examination, x-rays, scaling, polishing, fluoride treatments, pit and fissure sealant, subgingival root planning and curettage. Educate patients in the proper methods of oral hygiene and plaque control.</p> <p> </p> <p><span>Clinical</span></p> <ul> <li>Provides oral prophylaxis, scaling and root planning, sealants, dental and periodontal charting and topical preventive treatments for the patient population.  To meet productivity targets quarterly <li>Provides appropriate individualized patient education for maintenance of oral health.  Emphasizes preventive techniques and compliance with recall intervals. <li>Provides radiographic services. <li>Reviews patient’s medical history prior to start of visit. Maintains accurate documentation of dental hygiene services provided and a hygiene assessment including periodontal charting by completion of the electronic dental record at the end of each visit. <li>Maintains the treatment area, equipment, instruments and supplies in proper working order daily.  Strictly follows safety and infection control standards. <li>Shares responsibility for the maintenance of the logbook required documentation and task list including the autoclave with the dental assistant at a fixed site. <li>Ensures all electronic charting, documentation, and telephone encounters are in compliance with agency standards. </ul> <p> </p> <p><span>Administrative</span></p> <ul> <li>Participates in the assessment of dental services and quality assurance program. <li>Maintains regular communication with the dental director, staff dentists and office manager.  </ul> <p> </p> <p> </p> <p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p> <ul> <li>RDH degree from accredited dental hygiene school required. <li>Licensure – State of Connecticut dental hygiene license. <li>Minimum of 1 year clinical experience preferred <li>Interest in providing care to diverse patient population. <li>Commitment to preventive dental care. <li>For Mobile Dental program: Reliable access to an automobile and a valid driver’s license or reliable access to transportation to assigned work areas.    <li>Written and oral bilingual fluency in language spoken by our patient population (for example, English/Spanish) strongly preferred. <li>Requires as a condition of employment current American Red Cross CPR for the Professional Rescuer and AED (CPR/FPR/AED) certification. The only acceptable alternative is current American Heart Association BLS/AED for Healthcare Providers certification.  </ul> <p>#toponehire</p> ]]>
