ier scorecards and maintain supplier risk rating systems</p> <li> <p>Prepare operations reviews covering Supplier Quality KPIs, action plans, and audit schedules</p> <li> <p>Perform additional duties as assigned</p> </ul> <hr> <h3><strong>Qualifications</strong></h3> <ul> <li> <p>Bachelor’s Degree in Mechanical Engineering or equivalent</p> <li> <p>Strong working knowledge of Quality Management Systems (QMS) and industry standards</p> <li> <p>Minimum of <strong>3+ years</strong> of relevant experience in a similar role</p> <li> <p>Experience in <strong>metals manufacturing</strong> strongly preferred</p> </ul> <hr> <h3><strong>Working Conditions</strong></h3> <ul> <li> <p>Office environment within a manufacturing facility</p> </ul> <hr> <h3><strong>Physical Requirements</strong></h3> <ul> <li> <p>Ability to lift, move, and transport items weighing up to 20 lbs</p> <li> <p>Ability to operate a computer and office equipment for a minimum of 6 hours per day</p> <li> <p>Ability to remain stationary for extended periods and move throughout the facility as needed</p> <li> <p>Ability to detect and correct errors on paper and computer screens</p> <li> <p>Ability to communicate effectively verbally, nonverbally, and in writing</p> </ul> <hr> <h3><strong>Additional Information</strong></h3> <ul> <li> <p>Management reserves the right to assign or reassign duties at any time</p> <li> <p>Job description may be modified as business needs evolve</p> <li> <p>Must be able to perform essential job functions in accordance with ADA, FMLA, and applicable regulations</p> <li> <p>Regular, punctual attendance is required</p> <li> <p>Experience with Lean Manufacturing or a willingness to learn and participate is preferred</p> </ul> <hr> <ul> <li><span>#toponehire</span> </ul> ]]>
