<![CDATA[ <h2><span>Materials Manager Opening </span></h2> <p><span>Location: Kensington , CT<br /> Compensation: $135,000 base + 10% bonus<br /> Reports To: Director of Supply Chain<br /> Direct Reports: 5 (Logistics, Inventory & Purchasing)</span></p> <hr> <h3><span>Position Overview</span></h3> <p><span>We are conducting a new search for an experienced Materials Manager to lead logistics, inventory, and purchasing operations within a fast-paced manufacturing environment. This role is critical to ensuring material readiness, inventory accuracy, supplier performance, and on-time delivery while driving cost reduction and operational efficiency.</span></p> <p><span>The Materials Manager will partner closely with cross-functional leaders and senior management to support business growth, operational planning, and continuous improvement initiatives.</span></p> <hr> <h3><span>Key Responsibilities</span></h3> <ul> <li> <p><span>Lead and support Logistics, Inventory, and Purchasing teams to meet plant and business needs</span></p> <li> <p><span>Ensure material availability, inventory accuracy, shipment timeliness, and cost control</span></p> <li> <p><span>Implement and maintain standard work across all material functions</span></p> <li> <p><span>Oversee inventory cycle counts, adjustments, and material issue compliance</span></p> <li> <p><span>Drive purchasing performance metrics including:</span></p> <ul> </ul> <li> <p><span>PPV</span></p> <li> <p><span>On-time PO issuance</span></p> <li> <p><span>Supplier communication</span></p> <li> <p><span>Cost reduction initiatives</span></p> <li> <p><span>Long-Term Agreements (LTAs)</span></p> <li> <p><span>Lead time and terms negotiation</span></p> </ul> <li> <p><span>Participate in daily Tier walks and represent materials functions</span></p> <li> <p><span>Provide data-driven recommendations to senior leadership</span></p> <li> <p><span>Support Sales, Growth, and Operations Planning (GDP)</span></p> <li> <p><span>Ensure material readiness and risk mitigation for plant operations</span></p> <li> <p><span>Manage accuracy of on-hand inventory and purchase orders</span></p> <li> <p><span>Ensure timely PO releases within delegation of authority</span></p> <li> <p><span>Approve purchasing team expense reports and corporate card coding</span></p> <li> <p><span>Support government audits, compliance requirements, and supplier needs</span></p> <li> <p><span>Assist with year-end inventory processes</span></p> <li> <p><span>Monitor and improve KPIs including:</span></p> <ul> </ul> <li> <p><span>On-Time Delivery (OTD)</span></p> <li> <p><span>PPV</span></p> <li> <p><span>Inventory adjustments</span></p> <li> <p><span>Freight cost reduction</span></p> <li> <p><span>Ensure team members are properly trained and cross-trained</span></p> <hr> <h3><span>Supervisory Responsibilities</span></h3> <ul> <li> <p><span>Directly manage employees within Logistics, Inventory, and Purchasing</span></p> <li> <p><span>Interview, hire, train, coach, and develop team members</span></p> <li> <p><span>Assign work, set expectations, and evaluate performance</span></p> <li> <p><span>Address employee relations issues and resolve concerns in accordance with company policies and applicable laws</span></p> </ul> <hr> <h3><span>Qualifications</span></h3> <p><span>Education & Experience</span></p> <ul> <li> <p><span>Bachelor’s degree in Supply Chain, Business, Operations, or related field OR</span></p> <li> <p><span>5–7 years of related experience (or equivalent combination of education and experience)</span></p> <li> <p><span>Working knowledge of aerospace specifications and standards</span></p> <li> <p><span>2–4 years of experience in production control and/or inventory management</span></p> <li> <p><span>2–4 years of experience with Epicor or similar MRP/ERP systems</span></p> </ul> <p><span>Skills & Competencies</span></p> <ul> <li> <p><span>Intermediate to advanced Epicor (or similar MRP) experience</span></p> <li> <p><span>Strong Excel skills (pivot tables, VLOOKUP, data analysis)</span></p> <li> <p><span>Excellent communication, interpersonal, and leadership skills</span></p> <li> <p><span>Strong organizational skills with ability to manage multiple priorities</span></p> <li> <p><span>High level of accountability, independence, and follow-through</span></p> <li> <p><span>Proficient with Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint)</span></p> </ul> <hr> <h3><span>Work Environment & Physical Requirements</span></h3> <ul> <li> <p><span>Combination of standing, walking, and sitting</span></p> <li> <p><span>Frequent use of hands and arms</span></p> <li> <p><span>Occasional lifting up to 10 pounds</span></p> <li> <p><span>Vision requirements include close, distance, color, peripheral, and depth perception</span></p> </ul> <hr> <h3><span>Work Authorization</span></h3> <p><span>U.S. Citizenship is required due to ITAR compliance. Applicants must meet the definition of a “U.S. Person” under 22 C.F.R. §120.15.</span></p> <hr> <h3><span>Equal Opportunity Employer</span></h3> <p><span>This organization is an Equal Opportunity Employer and does not discriminate based on race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, national origin, veteran status, disability, or any other legally protected status.</span></p> <p> </p> <p><span><span>#toponehire</span></span></p> ]]>
