riances, recommending corrective actions. </span></span></span> <li><span><span><span>Analyze key business areas and collaborating closely with other departments. Examples include:</span></span></span> <ul> </ul> <li><span><span><span>Operations: Assess procurement, manufacturing, and distributions costs for variances and identify areas for optimization.</span></span></span> <li><span><span><span>Sales: Perform margin analysis, evaluate the impact of discounts, promotions, and pricing. </span></span></span> <li><span><span><span>Marketing: analyze ROI on marketing spend.</span></span></span> <li><span><span><span>Other: review G&A expenses and other operational costs </span></span></span> </ul> <p> </p> <ol> <li><span><span><strong><span><span>System Optimization:</span></span></strong></span></span> </ol> <p> </p> <ul> <li><span><span><span>Support optimization and ongoing maintenance of the Jet Analytics system to improve reporting accuracy and efficiency. </span></span></span> <li><span><span><span>Drive continuous improvements in financial data systems and reporting tools, ensuring data integrity and consistency.</span></span></span> </ul> <p> <span><span><strong>  </strong></span></span><br /> <span><span><strong><span><span>EXPECTATIONS</span></span></strong></span></span><br />  </p> <ol> <li><span><span><strong><span><span>Education & Experience:</span></span></strong></span></span> </ol> <p> </p> <ul> <li><span><span><span>Bachelor’s Degree in Finance, Accounting, Economics or other related field</span></span></span> <li><span><span><span>7+ years of experience in financial analysis or related field, with a demonstrated track record of complex financial modeling and analysis. <strong> </strong></span></span></span> </ul> <p> </p> <ol> <li><span><span><strong><span><span><span>Technical Proficiency:</span></span></span></strong></span></span> </ol> <p> </p> <ul> <li><span><span><strong><span>Advanced user of BC 14 – Microsoft Dynamics 365 Business Central and Jet Analytics or similar systems is required. </span></strong></span></span> <li><span><span><strong><span>Advanced proficiency in Microsoft Excel (Power Query & PowerPivot, and complex financial modeling expertise required).</span></strong></span></span> <li><span><span><strong><span>Experience with relational databases (SQL or similar) and financial data integration across platforms.</span></strong></span></span> <li><span><span><strong><span>Familiarity with business intelligence tools (e.g. Power BI) for data visualization and reporting. </span></strong></span></span> </ul> <p> </p> <ol> <li><span><span><strong><span><span>Analytical & Strategic Skills:</span></span></strong></span></span> </ol> <p> </p> <ul> <li><span><span><span>Expertise in advanced financial analysis techniques, including forecasting and variance analysis. </span></span></span> <li><span><span><span>Ability to translate complex financial data into actionable insights.</span></span></span> <li><span><span><span>Strong ability to identify financial trends, risks and opportunities. </span></span></span> </ul> <p> </p> <ol> <li><span><span><strong><span><span>Communication & Collaboration: </span></span></strong></span></span> </ol> <p> </p> <ul> <li><span><span><span>Strong verbal and written communications skills, with the ability to present complex financial data in a clear, concise manner. </span></span></span> <li><span><span><span>Proven ability to work collaboratively with cross-functional teams to integrate financial data across platforms, develop operational dashboards, and support data-driven decision-making at all levels of the organization. </span></span></span> <li><span><span><span>Proactive and self-directed, with a strong desire for continuous improvement and professional development. </span></span></span> </ul> <ul> <li><span><span><span>Demonstrated ability to lead financial projects and initiatives independently, managing multiple priorities and delivering high-quality results in a fast-paced environment.</span></span></span> </ul> <p>#toponehire</p> ]]>
