<![CDATA[ <p>TITLE: Senior Manufacturing Engineer<br /> COMPENSATION: $105,000 – $120,000<br /> LOCATION: Bolton, CT<br />  </p> <p>Note: Candidates with both mechanical and manufacturing engineering experience are strongly encouraged to apply.</p> <hr> <h3>Position Overview</h3> <p>We are seeking a highly experienced Senior Manufacturing Engineer to lead process optimization and production efficiency initiatives within an electronic component manufacturing environment. This is a hands-on technical role focused on process development, improving throughput, enhancing product quality, and ensuring manufacturing cost-effectiveness.</p> <hr> <h3>Key Responsibilities</h3> <p>As the Senior Manufacturing Engineer, you will be responsible for:</p> <ul> <li> <p>Innovating in wire-wound electrical component manufacturing and build-to-print process development</p> <li> <p>Leading lean manufacturing initiatives that improve efficiency, quality, and profitability</p> <li> <p>Optimizing work-cell layouts to enhance performance, safety, and ergonomics</p> <li> <p>Developing and implementing assembly procedures aligned with industry standards</p> <li> <p>Driving new process development and recommending capital investments to support growth</p> </ul> <hr> <h3>Preferred Knowledge, Skills & Abilities</h3> <ul> <li> <p>Experience working in AS9100 / ISO 9001 quality-managed manufacturing environments</p> <li> <p>Understanding of ASME Y14.5 GD&T</p> <li> <p>Lean manufacturing or Six Sigma training</p> <li> <p>Strong mechanical aptitude, including equipment setup and maintenance</p> <li> <p>Experience with electrical testing of components and assemblies</p> <li> <p>Knowledge of manufacturing processes, production equipment, and inspection methods</p> <li> <p>Proficiency in solid modeling software (Inventor, SolidWorks, NX, Catia) and ERP systems</p> <li> <p>Strong analytical and problem-solving abilities</p> <li> <p>Excellent verbal communication and technical writing skills</p> <li> <p>Ability to work collaboratively across departments and with external partners</p> <li> <p>High self-motivation, strong organization, and effective prioritization skills</p> <li> <p>Proficiency in Microsoft Office—Excel, Word, PowerPoint</p> <li> <p>Basic project scheduling experience with scheduling tools</p> <li> <p>Ability to adapt to changing customer and production requirements</p> <li> <p>Must be a U.S. Person as defined by ITAR</p> </ul> <hr> <h3>Education & Experience Requirements</h3> <ul> <li> <p>Bachelor’s degree in Manufacturing, Mechanical, Electrical, or Industrial Engineering (or similar)</p> <li> <p>Minimum 10 years of manufacturing experience, including at least 5 years with related products/processes</p> <li> <p>Prior leadership or supervisory experience preferred</p> </ul> <hr> <h3>Work Environment</h3> <p>This role includes both office work and hands-on shop floor involvement. You will work with office software and tools as well as manufacturing, machining, electrical test, and inspection equipment. Occasional travel between nearby facilities (within 1 mile) may be required.</p> <hr> <h3>Core Values</h3> <p>This employer values individuals who demonstrate:</p> <ul> <li> <p>Continuous Improvement: Learn – Teach – Grow</p> <li> <p>Accountability: Ownership – Procedure – Pride</p> <li> <p>Reliability: Honesty – Loyalty – Integrity</p> <li> <p>Engagement: Be Proactive – Help Others – Have Fun</p> <li> <p>Clear Communication: Identify – Communicate – Report</p> </ul> <hr> <h3><span>#toponehire</span></h3> ]]>
