<![CDATA[ <p><strong>Senior Data Vault Builder (Remote – EST Hours)</strong><br /> <strong>Compensation:</strong> $160,000 – $175,000<br /> <strong>Location:</strong> Fully Remote (U.S. – Eastern Time Zone)<br /> <strong>Category:</strong> Information Technology</p> <hr> <h3><strong>About the Opportunity</strong></h3> <p>We’re seeking an experienced <strong>Senior Data Vault Builder</strong> to design, implement, and maintain enterprise-scale Data Vault solutions supporting analytical and operational data needs. This is a <strong>hands-on technical position</strong> focused on architecting and optimizing Raw Vault, Business Vault, and Info Mart layers using Data Vault 2.0 methodologies.</p> <p>This opportunity is ideal for a <strong>seasoned data professional</strong> with deep expertise in VaultSpeed (or WhereScape 3D), strong SQL skills, and a solid understanding of data modeling, lineage, and performance optimization—particularly within <strong>Snowflake</strong> environments.</p> <hr> <h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3> <ul> <li> <p>Design, build, and maintain Raw Vault components (hubs, links, satellites) using VaultSpeed or similar tooling.</p> <li> <p>Develop and optimize Business Vault and Info Mart layers to support analytics and reporting.</p> <li> <p>Implement efficient ETL/ELT pipelines using SQL, views, stored procedures, and VaultSpeed-generated code.</p> <li> <p>Translate mapping documents and business rules into scalable Data Vault models.</p> <li> <p>Apply CDC (Change Data Capture) and SCD Type 2 logic for historical tracking.</p> <li> <p>Monitor, troubleshoot, and tune data pipeline performance across all vault layers.</p> <li> <p>Profile and validate source data for design alignment and accuracy.</p> <li> <p>Create clear technical documentation and data flow diagrams from source through vault layers.</p> <li> <p>Ensure compliance with data governance and metadata standards.</p> <li> <p>Collaborate closely with data architects, business SMEs, and analytics teams to ensure business alignment.</p> </ul> <hr> <h3><strong>Required Skills & Experience</strong></h3> <ul> <li> <p>8+ years of professional experience in data engineering or data warehousing.</p> <li> <p>Proven expertise building and maintaining all layers of the <strong>Data Vault (Raw, Business, and Info Mart)</strong>.</p> <li> <p>Proficiency with <strong>VaultSpeed</strong> or <strong>WhereScape 3D</strong> (and willingness to complete VaultSpeed training).</p> <li> <p>Advanced SQL development and performance tuning skills.</p> <li> <p>Experience designing and implementing <strong>Star Schema / Dimensional Models</strong>.</p> <li> <p>Strong understanding of <strong>data lineage, governance, and metadata management</strong>.</p> <li> <p>Hands-on experience in <strong>Snowflake</strong> environments.</p> <li> <p>Proficiency in <strong>erwin</strong> or similar data modeling tools.</p> <li> <p>Ability to provide occasional off-hours support as required.</p> </ul> <hr> <h3><strong>Preferred Qualifications</strong></h3> <ul> <li> <p><strong>Data Vault Certified Professional (DVCP) 2.1</strong> certification.</p> <li> <p>Experience integrating with BI or self-service analytics tools.</p> <li> <p>Familiarity with <strong>Agile/Scrum</strong> development methodologies.</p> <li> <p>Strong communication skills and ability to document complex data flows for both technical and business audiences.</p> </ul> <hr> <h3><strong>Education</strong></h3> <ul> <li> <p><strong>Bachelor’s degree</strong> in Computer Science, Information Systems, or a related field.</p> </ul> <hr> <h3><strong>Compensation & Employment Details</strong></h3> <ul> <li> <p><strong>Salary Range:</strong> $160,000 – $175,000 (based on experience, certifications, and technical proficiency).</p> <li> <p><strong>Schedule:</strong> Full-time, remote (must be available to work EST business hours).</p> <li> <p><strong>Work Authorization:</strong> U.S. work authorization required; sponsorship not available.</p> </ul> <p>#toponehire</p> ]]>
