<![CDATA[ <p><span><span><strong><span><span><span>RESPONSIBILITIES</span></span></span></strong></span></span></p> <p> <span><span>The Accounting & Systems Analyst plays a critical role in bridging accounting and operations by supporting core financial processes and enhancing systems efficiency. This position combines hands-on accounting for a select portfolio of properties with portfolio-wide financial analysis, budgeting, and reporting. As the analyst develops, they will take on increased responsibility for evaluating asset performance, implementing system improvements, and streamlining processes.</span></span><br /> <span><span>· Prepare monthly financial statements for assigned properties.</span></span><br /> <span><span>· Perform monthly variance analysis against budget, identifying drivers of favorable and unfavorable results; collaborating with Accountants, Property Managers, and Regional Managers.</span></span><br /> <span><span>· Support annual budget preparation, including utility consumption and rate analysis, and expense trend reviews.</span></span><br /> <span><span>· Prepare ad hoc reports such as overtime analysis, year-over-year comparisons, and unit turnover analysis.</span></span><br /> <span><span>· Assist in gathering and uploading audit documentation for external auditors.</span></span><br /> <span><span>· Prepare, maintain and track Replacement Reserve Draw requests; establish standard operating procedures.</span></span><br /> <span><span>· Provide operational and system support for budgets and financial reporting.</span></span><br /> <span><span>· Coordinate system upgrades and implement enhancements as familiarity with accounting processes grows.</span></span><br /> <span><span>· Identify opportunities to improve data integrity, reporting efficiency, and workflow automation.</span></span></p> <p> <span><span><strong><span><span><span>REQUIREMENTS</span></span></span></strong></span></span><br /> <span><span>· Bachelor’s degree in Accounting, Finance, or related field.</span></span><br /> <span><span>· 3+ years of relevant experience in accounting, finance, or a similar role; real estate industry experience preferred.</span></span><br /> <span><span>· Requires knowledge of financial terms, concepts and accounting principles with ability to comprehend, analyze, interpret and extract data from various sources.</span></span><br /> <span><span>· Advanced excel skills, including PivotTables, Power Query, INDEX/MATCH, XLOOKUP, dynamic arrays, and advanced formulas (nested logic functions) for complex data analysis and automation.</span></span><br /> <span><span>· Familiarity with accounting & property management systems (RealPage) preferred.</span></span><br /> <span><span>· Excellent verbal and written communication skills</span></span></p> <p> </p> <p>#toponehire</p> ]]>
