<![CDATA[ <p><span><span><strong><span>One of our top clients is looking to add an Accountant to the team!  This role will focus on general accounting activities for the company, and involved in AP, AR, and GL duties.</p> <p> Schedule: Hybrid/Remote depending on candidate preferences  <br /> HQ is in North Kingstown, RI<br /> Controller looking to bring on an Accountant to support accounting process.</span></strong></span></span></p> <p> <span><span><strong><span><span>Skills</span></span></strong></span></span></p> <ul> <li><span><span><span>Ability to foster teamwork and work inside of a team</span></span></span> <li><span><span><span>Ability to identify and seek needed information/research</span></span></span> <li><span><span><span>Ability to meet deadlines</span></span></span> <li><span><span><span>Manage all aspects of Accounts Receivable from invoicing to cash collection including contacting customers</span></span></span> <li><span><span><span>Mathematical and Accounting skills</span></span></span> <li><span><span><span>Analytical thinking skills & Detail oriented</span></span></span> <li><span><span><span>Bilingual Written and Verbal communication skills – English & Spanish</span></span></span> <li><span><span><span>Advanced Excel Skills</span></span></span> <li><span><span><span>V, H, X Lookups</span></span></span> <li><span><span><span>Pivot Tables</span></span></span> <li><span><span><span>Power Query</span></span></span> <li><span><span><span>Index Match</span></span></span> <li><span><span><span>Conditional & Custom Formatting</span></span></span> </ul> <p><span><span><strong><span><span>Job Summary</span></span></strong></span></span><br /> <span><span>Lead and manage the Accounts Receivable and Accounts Payable processes for the company.  Provides assistance to the Controller in managing the accounting operations of the organization.  Interact with different functional departments to either obtain or provide requested information.  Basic knowledge of cost accounting.  Work with individuals remotely, possibly in different time zones, to gather information and complete tasks.  Participate in the month, quarter and year end closing processes.</span></span></p> <p> <span><span><strong><span><span>Job Duties</span></span></strong></span></span><br /> <span><span><span>Control over the Accounts Receivable and participates in the Accounts Payable processes.  Contacting both customers and vendors as needed.  Review bank activity and record customer payments.  Prepare weekly reports for management and owners.  Assists the Controller with the monthly, quarterly, and annual accounting close processes.  Prepares financial statements and filings in compliance with GAAP.    Assists in ad hoc analyses of the organization’s finances and prepares reports to facilitate decision making.  Administers internal controls and audits of policies and procedures meant to preserve the organization’s assets. </span></span></span><br /> <span><span><strong><span><span>Experience and Education</span></span></strong></span></span><br /> <span><span><span>Serves as leader of authority with expert-level knowledge in one or more areas.  Makes decisions and recommendations.  Plans, organizes, and guides projects with fellow employees.  Performs work under minimal supervision.  Handles complex issues and problems and refers only the most complex issues to higher-level staff.  Possesses comprehensive knowledge of subject matter.  May act as a lead.  Typically requires a bachelor’s degree and 2 to 5 years of experience.  A master’s degree, CPA license or CPA candidate may be preferred. </span></span></span><br /> <span><span><strong><span><span>Reports to</span></span></strong></span></span><br /> <span><span><span>Controller and CFO </span></span></span></p> <p> . . . Pay Statement and Pay Transparency Laws: rate of pay listed is on a per hour basis. You will be entitled to health insurance once employed for 60 days and you must work 30 hours per week, on average, per month to enroll and maintain health insurance through Complete Staffing Solutions. Once both qualifiers are met you must complete the enrollment packet and your benefits will start on the first of the subsequent month. . . It is our policy to provide equal employment opportunity to all individuals regardless of race, color, sex, sexual orientation, religion, disability, age, veteran status, ancestry, national or ethnic origin or any other legally protected class. We are committed to a diverse workforce. We value all employees’ talents and support an environment that is inclusive and respectful. We are strongly committed to this policy, and believe in the concept and spirit of the law. #toponehire</p> ]]>
