or junior associates and participate in internal training and professional development sessions</p> </ul> <h3><strong>Qualifications</strong></h3> <ul> <li> <p>3+ years of client service experience in Employee Benefits or insurance brokerage (varies by role level)</p> <li> <p>Strong understanding of health and welfare benefits programs, compliance, and market trends</p> <li> <p>Excellent communication, organization, and analytical skills</p> <li> <p>Proven ability to manage multiple clients and projects in a fast-paced environment</p> <li> <p>Relevant insurance licensing (or ability to obtain upon hire)</p> </ul> <h3><strong>Why Join</strong></h3> <ul> <li> <p>Hybrid work schedule based in West Hartford, CT</p> <li> <p>Competitive base salary with performance-based bonus potential</p> <li> <p>Comprehensive benefits package and generous paid time off</p> <li> <p>12-week paid parental leave</p> <li> <p>Opportunities for professional growth and advancement through paid training and certifications</p> <li> <p>Supportive, community-driven culture that celebrates achievement and promotes well-being</p> </ul> <p>#toponehire</p> ]]>
