urance claims, or a legal/paralegal setting preferred</p> <li> <p>Knowledge of healthcare, casualty, or property insurance</p> <li> <p>Proficiency in Microsoft Word and Excel; strong general computer skills</p> <li> <p>Ability to interpret EOBs, UB-04s, SPDs, and similar healthcare documents</p> <li> <p>Strong analytical, written, and verbal communication skills</p> <li> <p>Excellent organizational skills and attention to detail</p> <li> <p>Ability to manage multiple deadlines and high-volume caseloads</p> <li> <p>Team-oriented attitude with the ability to work independently</p> </ul> <h4><strong>Compensation & Benefits</strong></h4> <ul> <li> <p>Base salary: <strong>$60,000–$75,000</strong> (based on experience)</p> <li> <p><strong>Incentive compensation</strong> based on recovery performance — potential to match or exceed base salary over time</p> <li> <p>Comprehensive benefits package, including medical, dental, disability, and retirement plan</p> <li> <p>Paid time off and opportunities for professional growth</p> </ul> <h4><strong>Physical Requirements</strong></h4> <ul> <li> <p>Prolonged periods of sitting or standing</p> <li> <p>Frequent use of computer and phone systems</p> <li> <p>Ability to work in a secure, dedicated workspace</p> </ul> <hr> <p><strong>Join a team that’s making a measurable impact in healthcare cost recovery.</strong><br /> Apply today to take your career in subrogation to the next level!</p> <p> </p> <p>#toponehire</p> ]]>
