ofessional and ethical approach in all business dealings.</p> </ul> <hr> <h3><strong>Qualifications</strong></h3> <ul> <li> <p><strong>Education:</strong> High school diploma or equivalent required; bachelor’s degree preferred.</p> <li> <p><strong>Experience:</strong> Minimum of 10 years in sales, account management, or customer service.</p> <li> <p>Experience selling into <strong>semiconductor</strong> or <strong>medical device manufacturing</strong> markets is highly desirable.</p> <li> <p>Strong understanding of <strong>manufacturing and supply chain processes</strong> preferred.</p> <li> <p>Proven ability to build customer relationships and manage expectations.</p> <li> <p>Excellent communication, negotiation, and problem-solving skills.</p> <li> <p>Ability to quote pricing accurately and manage delivery expectations.</p> <li> <p>Must demonstrate a strong commitment to quality, ethics, and customer satisfaction.</p> </ul> <hr> <h3><strong>Physical & Work Requirements</strong></h3> <ul> <li> <p>Ability to work seated for extended periods (in office, during travel, or on flights).</p> <li> <p>Manual dexterity for data entry and administrative work.</p> <li> <p>Ability to bend, reach, and lift up to 25–30 lbs.</p> <li> <p>Must be comfortable working in an office or industrial environment with potential exposure to heat, noise, or fumes.</p> <li> <p>Strong written and verbal communication skills required.</p> </ul> <hr> <h3><strong>Compensation & Benefits</strong></h3> <ul> <li> <p><strong>Base Salary:</strong> $110,000 – $125,000</p> <li> <p><strong>Incentives:</strong> Up to 100% of base salary potential after one year</p> <li> <p><strong>Bonus Schedule:</strong> Quarterly and annual components based on performance</p> <li> <p>Competitive benefits package and opportunities for professional growth.</p> </ul> <hr> <h3><strong>Equal Opportunity Statement</strong></h3> <p>We are proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer. Employment decisions are made without regard to