> <p>College or technical degree in mechanical, electrical, or industrial maintenance preferred; high school diploma plus 5+ years industrial maintenance required.</p> <li> <p>Advanced training in electrical systems and strong mechanical troubleshooting skills.</p> <li> <p>Hands-on experience with <strong>furnaces/heat treating equipment</strong> is required.</p> <li> <p>Proficiency in welding, cutting, brazing, and knowledge of hydraulics.</p> <li> <p>Ability to read and interpret blueprints and technical manuals.</p> <li> <p>Strong leadership skills with experience supervising maintenance staff.</p> <li> <p>Computer proficiency, including Microsoft Office.</p> <li> <p>Ability to work overtime, weekends, and on-call as needed.</p> <li> <p>Must be able to work in industrial environments (heat, noise, confined spaces, heights) and lift up to 35 lbs.</p> </ul> <hr> <h3><strong>Why Join Us</strong></h3> <ul> <li> <p>Competitive base salary with performance bonus</p> <li> <p>Comprehensive benefits package</p> <li> <p>Opportunity to lead maintenance operations for a critical manufacturing process</p> <li> <p>Work in a dynamic, safety-focused industrial environment</p> </ul> <hr> <p><strong>Apply today to be considered for this exciting Maintenance Manager opportunity in Highland Heights, OH.</strong></p> <p> </p> <p> </p> <p>#toponehire</p> ]]>
