<![CDATA[ <p><strong>CNC MILLING MACHINIST<br /> COMPENSATION- $30.00/HR<br /> LOCATION: NEW BRITAIN CT</p> <p> Job Summary:</strong></p> <p>The Level 3 CNC Milling Machinist at a minimum performs machine setups on 3 and 4 axis CNC Milling Machines. 5 axis Machine setups as allowed with applicable skill level / experience. Performs necessary inspection steps. Makes necessary minor adjustments as required. Operates production on 3, 4, and 5 axis machines as necessary.</p> <p> <strong>Duties / Re</strong><strong>sponsibilities:</strong></p> <ul> <li>Performing machine setups quickly, accurately, and efficiently on all 3 and 4 Axis milling equipment. 5 axis setups as skill level / experience allows. <li>Loading, proving out, and maintenance of CNC programs. <li>Operating machines to produce production runs of parts as needed including operating controls, setting offsets, and performing simple edits. <li>Inspecting of parts for conformance to requirements of Process / Inspection sheets and customer drawings. <li>Communicating with supervisor, engineers, production control, quality and other shop personnel for assignments and to report machining, equipment or quality issues. <li>Keeping equipment and work area clean and orderly. Perform basic preventative maintenance functions on equipment. <li>Maintaining lot control and quality standards through understanding of the Quality Management System <li>Monitoring and documenting operational and performance issues and provide feedback to supervisor as required <li>Develop and maintain effective working relationships with peers, supervisors, and other staff <li>Within the scope of the job requirements, will be required to adhere and comply with state and federal law, the Company AS9100 quality program and procedures, Company policies and Safety and Environmental regulations <li>Other duties as directed by supervisor. </ul> <p><strong>Required Skills / Abilities:</strong></p> <ul> <li>Proficient knowledge and application of precision measuring instruments and the application of such instruments. Instruments should include but not limited to Micro-Height Gages, Micrometers, Calipers, Depth gages, Indicators, Dial Bore Gages. <li>Strong skills inspecting and verifying finished products. <li>G & M code fluency and ability to make minor edits in CNC programs <li>Knowledge of reading drawings and specifications with an understanding of geometric tolerance and dimensions. <li>Knowledge of tool holders, cutting tools, boring bars, fixtures, inserts and other accessories used on various machines. <li>Must be able to follow written and oral instructions <li>Strong verbal communication and problem-solving skills <li>Attention to detail and ability to deal with complexity <li>Capable of working in a customer-focused, deadline-driven environment while maintaining a positive attitude <li>Interested in learning with, and from, peers, engineering, and programming team to improve operations <li>Willing to run multiple machines independently or in a team environment. <li>CNC Turning experience a plus </ul> <p><strong>Education and Experience:</strong></p> <ul> <li>Minimum of 3-5 years CNC milling machine experience within an Aerospace machining, job shop environment. <li>High School Diploma or GED. <li>Technical/Vocational training welcome. </ul> <p><strong>Physical Requirements:</strong></p> <ul> <li>Must be able to lift 25 pounds </ul> <p>#toponehire</p> ]]>
