<![CDATA[ <h3>Quality Engineer</h3> <p>Location: Rutland, Vermont<br /> Compensation: $80,000 – $85,000<br /> Industry: Aerospace / Manufacturing / Quality Assurance</p> <hr> <h3>About the Opportunity</h3> <p>A leading precision manufacturing company in the Rutland, VT area is seeking a Quality Engineer to join its team. This role plays a vital part in maintaining and improving quality systems, ensuring compliance with AS9100, ISO 9001, and NADCAP, and driving continuous improvement initiatives across production processes.</p> <p>This is an excellent opportunity for a hands-on quality professional who thrives in a fast-paced, technical environment and enjoys solving complex problems that directly impact product quality and customer satisfaction.</p> <hr> <h3>Key Responsibilities</h3> <ul> <li> <p>Develop, implement, and maintain quality control systems and procedures to ensure consistent product and process integrity.</p> <li> <p>Perform internal audits to ensure compliance with AS9100, ISO9001, and NADCAP standards; identify and lead corrective actions for areas of improvement.</p> <li> <p>Lead Root Cause Corrective Action (RCCA) investigations and manage follow-up to prevent recurrence.</p> <li> <p>Interface directly with customers regarding product quality issues, corrective actions, and preventive measures.</p> <li> <p>Conduct PFMEAs and lead risk-reduction efforts using Six Sigma methodologies.</p> <li> <p>Monitor and maintain quality-related instruments, including calibration, testing, and process control systems.</p> <li> <p>Participate in receiving inspection, final inspection, and contract review processes.</p> <li> <p>Prepare and sign certifications and technical reports as required.</p> <li> <p>Identify quality training needs and help develop training programs to support continuous improvement.</p> <li> <p>Support safety, housekeeping, and compliance efforts across all quality and production activities.</p> <li> <p>Act as backup to the Quality Manager when required.</p> </ul> <hr> <h3>Qualifications</h3> <ul> <li> <p>U.S. Citizenship or Permanent Residency required (ITAR compliance).</p> <li> <p>Bachelor’s degree in Engineering or a related technical field preferred.</p> <li> <p>Minimum 3–5 years of experience in quality engineering or aerospace manufacturing environment.</p> <li> <p>Knowledge of AS9100, ISO9001, and NADCAP quality systems.</p> <li> <p>Proficiency in Microsoft Office (Excel – pivot tables, advanced formulas).</p> <li> <p>Strong ability to read and interpret blueprints, specifications, and technical documentation.</p> <li> <p>Excellent analytical, problem-solving, and written communication skills.</p> <li> <p>Six Sigma Green Belt preferred (or willingness to obtain).</p> <li> <p>Demonstrated ability to manage multiple priorities and meet deadlines.</p> </ul> <p>#toponehire</p> ]]>
