<![CDATA[ <h1><strong>Strategic Sales / Business Development Manager</strong></h1> <p><strong>Location:</strong> Central ADE Region<br /> <strong>Reports To:</strong> Regional Sales Manager</p> <hr> <h3><strong>Position Summary</strong></h3> <p>Based in the Central ADE Region, and reporting to the Regional Sales Manager, you will drive business growth. You will be responsible for prospecting new business opportunities, building long-term partnerships, cultivating strategic relationships, and collaborating with internal teams to craft strategies to deliver short-term and long-term growth. This role demands a proactive and strategic approach to sales, as well as a deep understanding of our heat treating services, to meet the needs of both new and existing customers.</p> <hr> <h3><strong>Essential Job Functions (Duties and Responsibilities)</strong></h3> <p>The primary duties consist of, but are not limited to, the following:</p> <ul> <li> <p>Identify, target, and secure new business opportunities by leveraging market insights and company offerings. Engage with potential clients to understand their needs and present tailored solutions.</p> <li> <p>Build and maintain strong, lasting relationships with key accounts and industry influencers. Work to expand existing accounts by identifying new revenue streams and optimizing service offerings.</p> <li> <p>Develop and execute strategic account plans.</p> <li> <p>Execute key account management. Develop multiple customer touchpoints and conduct regular visits to customer sites to build relationships, gather feedback, and identify opportunities for improvement.</p> <li> <p>Deliver presentations, seminars, and workshops to educate customers about the company’s offerings.</p> <li> <p>Leverage Salesforce.com reporting and dashboards to provide accurate forecasts and timely reporting on sales activities, including pipeline development, new account acquisition, and competitor analysis.</p> <li> <p>Stay up to date on industry trends, competitor activities, and market conditions. Share insights with the team to ensure the company remains competitive and responsive to customer needs.</p> <li> <p>Travel extensively (greater than 50%) to meet with customers and prospects. Attend industry events and conferences to build networks and enhance the company brand.</p> <li> <p>Performs other tasks as assigned or dictated by position.</p> <li> <p>Must have the ability to report for work on time, follow directions, interact effectively with co-workers, understand and follow rules and procedures, and accept constructive criticism.</p> </ul> <hr> <h3><strong>Qualifications</strong></h3> <p>To perform this job successfully, an individual must be able to perform each essential duty satisfactorily. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.</p> <ul> <li> <p><strong>ITAR Compliance:</strong> This position must satisfy ITAR requirements; candidates must be U.S. Citizens or Permanent Resident Card Holders.</p> <li> <p><strong>Experience:</strong> Minimum of 5 years in strategic sales or business development with proven success in driving revenue growth and securing new business.</p> <li> <p><strong>Industry Knowledge:</strong> Familiarity with heat treatment processes and the aerospace, automotive, or other relevant industries is a plus. Knowledge of metal processing, materials science, or engineering is beneficial.</p> <li> <p><strong>Sales & Negotiation Skills:</strong> Strong background in consultative selling, account management, and contract negotiations.</p> <li> <p><strong>Communication:</strong> Excellent interpersonal, presentation, and communication skills; ability to build rapport and influence at all levels.</p> <li> <p><strong>Education:</strong> Bachelor’s degree in Business, Engineering, or related field preferred.</p> <li> <p><strong>Technical Aptitude:</strong> Ability to engage in technical discussions with clients; understanding of customer requirements and company offerings.</p> <li> <p><strong>CRM Experience:</strong> Proven Salesforce (SFDC) proficiency for pipeline management, customer interactions, and data-driven growth strategies.</p> <li> <p><strong>Other Requirements:</strong></p> <ul> <li> <p>Valid driver’s license with ability to travel >50%.</p> <li> <p>Proficiency with Microsoft Office Suite and CRM tools.</p> <li> <p>Ability to read, write, and communicate effectively in English.</p> <li> <p>Strong judgment, problem-solving skills, and ability to resolve customer issues.</p> <li> <p>Advocate for quality in products and services.</p> <li> <p>Commitment to ethics in all interactions.</p> <li> <p>Ability to cultivate and develop customers from entrepreneurial businesses to multinational corporations.</p> </ul> </ul> <hr> <h3><strong>Physical & Mental Demands</strong></h3> <p>The following consist of, but are not limited to:</p> <ul> <li> <p>Ability to work in office or industrial environments.</p> <li> <p>Ability to sit, drive, and travel for extended periods.</p> <li> <p>Must manage multiple priorities and handle stressful situations.</p> <li> <p>Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.</p> <li> <p>Manual dexterity for data entry.</p> <li> <p>Ability to bend, pull, stoop, and reach as needed.</p> <li> <p>Ability to lift 25–30 lbs.</p> <li> <p>May be exposed to heat, fumes, noise, and humidity.</p> <li> <p>Must have cognitive and mental capacity to perform essential job functions.</p> <li> <p>Effective verbal and written communication skills.</p> <li> <p>Visual acuity for reading documents, computer screens, and files.</p> <li> <p>Ability to hear in person and via phone.</p> </ul> <hr> <h3><strong>Additional Information</strong></h3> <p>The statements herein are intended to describe the general nature and levels of work performed but are not a complete list of responsibilities, duties, and skills required. This job description does not constitute a written or implied contract for employment. The Company reserves the right to revise or change job duties and responsibilities as the need arises.</p> <hr> <p> </p> <p>#toponehire</p> ]]>
