<![CDATA[ <h1>Maintenance Supervisor</h1> <h2>Essential Job Functions (Duties and Responsibilities)</h2> <p>The primary duties consist of, but are not limited to, the following:</p> <ul> <li> <p>Supervise employees who perform maintenance and install equipment used in thermal processing applications.</p> <li> <p>Monitor, reinforce, and oversee health, safety, and environmental (EHS) performance of the department and employees.</p> <li> <p>Resolve chronic or acute equipment issues.</p> <li> <p>Identify, select, assign, and supervise contract personnel who perform specialized maintenance work or supplement department work.</p> <li> <p>Monitor progress of employees in skills training and identify/assign training as required.</p> <li> <p>Direct the scheduling of daily and monthly routine, equipment calibration, and preventive maintenance activities; coordinate with operations on scheduling shutdown equipment.</p> <li> <p>Utilize computerized maintenance management software (CMMS) for work order management, documenting equipment information, and managing preventive maintenance requirements.</p> <li> <p>Create, edit, or revise less complex engineering drawings using computer-aided engineering software.</p> <li> <p>Supervise warehouse shipping and receiving personnel; ensure spare parts inventory is available and managed properly.</p> <li> <p>Work closely with equipment vendors and suppliers on identifying/ordering specialty equipment or parts; review vendor/supplier performance objectively.</p> <li> <p>Evaluate and provide performance feedback both informally and through formal performance management systems.</p> <li> <p>Manage capital projects, including initiating Capital Asset Requests, purchasing requests for CapEx items, and supervising installations and project milestones.</p> <li> <p>Maintain fiscal budget responsibility through organized purchase order management and competitive supplier bidding.</p> <li> <p>Assess facility conditions and initiate repairs/maintenance activities.</p> <li> <p>Maintain argon and nitrogen gas inventories and delivery paperwork.</p> <li> <p>Prepare month-end reporting and update facility maintenance and Environmental Management System KPIs.</p> <li> <p>Report for work on time, follow directions, interact effectively with co-workers, understand and follow rules/procedures, and accept constructive criticism.</p> <li> <p>Handle confidential compensation information appropriately, without disclosing pay of employees/applicants.</p> </ul> <hr> <h2>Qualifications</h2> <p>To perform this job successfully, an individual must be able to perform each essential duty satisfactorily. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities.</p> <ul> <li> <p>Four-year college degree in Engineering, Industrial Technology, or related discipline preferred.</p> <li> <p>Five (5) years supervisory experience.</p> <li> <p>Ten (10) years cumulative maintenance experience in an industrial environment.</p> <li> <p>Deep and thorough knowledge of industrial manufacturing systems and heavy-duty piping and plumbing.</p> <li> <p>Experience with cooling water systems and water treatment.</p> <li> <p>Experience with cryogenics and high-pressure gas systems.</p> <li> <p>Basic electrical troubleshooting skills.</p> <li> <p>Basic hydraulic troubleshooting skills.</p> <li> <p>Computer proficiency.</p> </ul> <hr> <h2>Physical & Mental Demands</h2> <ul> <li> <p>Must be able to work in a sitting/standing position for extended periods in an industrial environment.</p> <li> <p>Manual dexterity to perform data entry functions.</p> <li> <p>Ability to bend, pull, stoop, and reach.</p> <li> <p>Ability to lift up to 35 lbs.</p> <li> <p>Exposure to heat, cold, noise, dust, humidity, fumes, argon and nitrogen gas lines/valve panels (high pressure), and chemical solvents.</p> <li> <p>May be required to work overtime or any shift, including weekends.</p> <li> <p>Must have the cognitive and mental capacity to perform essential job functions.</p> <li> <p>Must be self-directed and capable of multi-tasking.</p> <li> <p>Must be able to communicate effectively orally and in writing.</p> <li> <p>Visual acuity to read documents, computer screens, and files.</p> <li> <p>Ability to hear in person and via phone.</p> <p>#toponehire</p> </ul> ]]>
